tafsir[17]{c,v,t}:
  83,35,"On decorated couches they will look at the everlasting bliss that Allah prepared for them."
  83,36,"The disbelievers have been given the humiliating punishment as recompense of the actions they did in the world."
  84,1,"When the sky ruptures because of the angels descending from it."
  84,3,"When the earth is stretched by Allah as leather is stretched."
  84,4,"And throws out the treasures and the dead in it and becomes rid of them."
  84,8,"He will have an easy reckoning by Allah and his actions will be presented to Him without his being taken to task."
  84,9,"And he will return to his family delighted."
  84,10,"As for him who is given his book in his left hand behind his back."
  84,11,"He will call out for destruction to himself."
  84,12,"And he will enter the fire of Hell to suffer from its heat."
  84,13,"In the world he was amongst his family rejoicing with his acts of disbelief and sins."
  84,14,"He thought that he will not come back to life after death."
  84,16,"Allah took an oath by the redness that is in the horizon after the sun sets."
  84,17,"And He took an oath by the night and what is gathered therein."
  84,18,"And the moon when it comes together and is complete becoming a full moon."
  84,20,"What is the matter with these disbelievers who do not have faith in Allah and the last day?!"
  84,23,"Allah knows well what is contained in their hearts. Nothing of their actions is hidden from Him."